###<a id='resource-config'></a> Resource Config

VMs used by **Pivotal Container Service** jobs must meet the following minimum requirements:
  <table>
    <tr>
      <th>CPU</th>
      <th>Memory</th>
      <th>Disk</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>2</td>
      <td>8&nbsp;GB</td>
      <td>29&nbsp;GB</td>
    </tr>
  </table>
<p class="note"><strong>Note</strong>: If you experience timeouts or slowness when interacting with the PKS API, select a <strong>VM Type</strong> with greater CPU and memory resources.</p>

To deploy <strong>Pivotal Container Service</strong> job VMs meeting the minimum requirements, 
perform the following steps:

1. Click **Resource Config**.  
<br>
    The default "Automatic" <b>VM Type</b> does not meet the <strong>Pivotal Container Service</strong> job VM minimum requirements:  
    ![Resource pane configuration](images/resources-vsphere.png)
1. Select a <strong>VM Type</strong> with CPU, memory and disk resources either matching or exceeding 
the minimum <strong>Pivotal Container Service</strong> job VM requirements.
1. Select **Save**.  

